text.tspan: The search is based on terms retrieved by the Name Entity Recognitions which identify different
kinds of entities in a text. Among all the possible
entities provided by the library, we choose to base
the Wikipedia research on the entity recognized as
Person and Organization; we choose to use only
these two types because we notice an improvement in
the number and quality of the triples at the
end of the process.
The alias resolution process, on the other hand, takes
place after extracting SRO triples from the text;
it searches through the identified nodes (Subject
- Object), searching for the term on Wikipedia. If
a
node’s corresponding page ID (in Wikipedia) is the
same as another node, then they are aliases. If an
alias is detected, we add an edge between the two
nodes, like in the image example below.
In order to decide if the implementation of the Wikipedia
research improves indeed the result, we
decide to conduct the analysis of a text with and
without Wikipedia and compare the results.
As we can see in the table below the number of nodes
and relationships is significantly higher with
the extraction of information from Wikipedia.
Nodes
Relationships
Text
Text + Wikipedia
The number of nodes and relationships of the graphs
give us only an estimation of the volume of
information retrieved by the program but do not represent
the quality of the data.
To give an idea if the system really improves with
the use of Wikipedia we execute a query, which
retrieves the in-going and out-goings relationships
and nodes with the target “William henry gates
iii”. This will give us suggestions about the quality
of data on the subject of the text i.e Bill gates.
Specifically, the query is the following:
MATCH (n {name:"william henry gates iii"})-[r]-(m)
RETURN n,r,m
Using the User interface of neo4j, the images below
show the results of the execution of the query
with and without Wikipedia.
As we can see, the execution of the query on the configuration
without Wikipedia retrieved “title”
relationships and information about the origin and
date of birth of the Bill gates. The same query
performed on the Wikipedia configuration results in
the enrichments of the previous nodes with the
foundation of Microsoft, the alias node Bill gates
and the title of author.
